---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NavBar from '../components/NavBar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';

const EFFECTIVE_DATE = 'July 1, 2026';
---

<Layout title="Terms and conditions — Free Format Convert" description="The terms and conditions governing your use of Free Format Convert.">
	<NavBar />
	<main>
		<PageHeader title="Terms and conditions" subtitle={`Effective ${EFFECTIVE_DATE}`} />
		<section class="terms-body">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="prose">
					<p>
						These terms govern your use of Free Format Convert (the "Service"), a browser-based file conversion tool. By using
						the Service, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, please don't use the Service.
					</p>

					<h2>1. What the service does</h2>
					<p>
						Free Format Convert converts image, audio, and video files between formats. All conversion happens locally in your
						browser — your files are never uploaded to, or processed on, our servers. The only network activity the
						Service performs is downloading its own conversion engine (WebAssembly code) from a public CDN.
					</p>

					<h2>2. Your files and content</h2>
					<p>
						You retain all rights to any file you convert using the Service. Since files never leave your device, we
						have no access to, copy of, or control over your content at any point.
					</p>
					<p>You're responsible for making sure you have the right to convert and use any file you process with the Service.</p>

					<h2>3. Acceptable use</h2>
					<p>You agree not to use the Service to:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Convert files you don't have the legal right to possess or modify</li>
						<li>Attempt to disrupt, reverse-engineer, or overload the Service beyond normal use</li>
						<li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>4. No warranty</h2>
					<p>
						The Service is provided "as is," without warranty of any kind. Conversion quality, output fidelity, and
						format compatibility can vary by browser and by file. We don't guarantee the Service will be uninterrupted,
						error-free, or fit for any particular purpose.
					</p>

					<h2>5. Limitation of liability</h2>
					<p>
						To the fullest extent permitted by law, Free Format Convert and its operators are not liable for any indirect,
						incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Service, including loss of data or
						files processed locally in your browser.
					</p>

					<h2>6. Changes to these terms</h2>
					<p>
						We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of the Service after a change means you accept
						the updated terms. We'll update the effective date above when that happens.
					</p>

					<h2>7. Contact</h2>
					<p>
						Questions about these terms? Reach out via our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
	.terms-body {
		padding-bottom: var(--space-5xl);
	}
</style>
